  "analyst_notes": "Adani Power is India's largest private thermal power producer with an almost pure-coal portfolio (99.7%). With complete financial data, all 5 B5 credit metrics PASS - exceptionally strong balance sheet (Debt/EBITDA 1.24x, Interest Coverage 8.3x, FFO/Debt 40.6%, Current Ratio 1.62x, Debt/Capital 44.7%). B5 will now PASS, improving score to 3/5. However, significant transition risk remains: (1) No net-zero commitment; (2) No SBTi submission; (3) No coal exit plan; (4) Aggressive expansion from 15.2 GW to 41.87 GW coal by FY32; (5) Potential 200 MtCO2/year emissions at full expansion. B4 FAILS due to complete absence of transition commitments. B1 FAILS (100% coal at-risk). B2 PASSES narrowly at 19.1% CCE. Note: Adani Power is separate from Adani Green Energy (AGEL), which has distinct net-zero commitments. Emissions intensity of 853 kg CO2/MWh is high but in line with coal-dominated fleet. Expected score: 3/5 Medium (passes B2, B3, B5; fails B1, B4)."
